<td>"For different type of separations, Notice Period shall be either by employee or by employer. E.g. In case of Termination, employer has to give the notice period whereas in case of Resignation, employee has to give the notice period and so on. Whether Notice Period is by employee or by employer shall be maintained for the Separation Types.</td>
<td>NA</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>'Notice Amount (Days)' shall be the no. of days for which the Notice Amount is to be calculated. This days shall be obtained based on 'Notice Period Applicable Type' of the separation type, Notice Period By Employee (days) / Notice Period By Employer (days) applicable for the employee, Date and Effective Date in the Action Form."</td>
<td>You can set this entity-wise by selecting the appropriate entity type from the Entity dropdown field. Once done, you will have an option under the entity type in the Card Master to set value specific to each entity.</td>
